						<div class="body">@Anant, <br />
There is indeed a way to do that. <br />
You can cherry-pick the latest commit from the feature branch and apply it to the mainline(master). <br />
In case you are not authorized to push directly to master, you can create a new branch, cherry-pick the latest commit from your feature branch to the newly created branch, and then raise a pull request of your newly-created branch.<br />
<br />
Command - <br />
[newly-created-branch] git cherry-pick <latest-commit-id-from-your-feature-branch></div> 
