							<span class="author">CicheR</span> on 
							<span class="date">June 17, 2020 at 17:20</span>
						</div> 
						<div class="body">If it's only about squashing the lasts N commits, maybe the easyest way is:<br />
 `git reset --soft HEAD~N`<br />
That will remove the last N commits and leaves all the changes of the commits as staged changes. <br />
Then, simply commit again:<br />
`git commit -m"New commit message"`</div> 
					</div>
